.TH "gen_pool_dma_zalloc_align" 9 "gen_pool_dma_zalloc_align" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gen_pool_dma_zalloc_align \- allocate special zeroed memory from the pool for DMA usage with the given alignment
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" gen_pool_dma_zalloc_align
.BI "(struct gen_pool *pool "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t *dma "  ","
.BI "int align "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pool" 12
pool to allocate from
.IP "size" 12
number of bytes to allocate from the pool
.IP "dma" 12
DMA-view physical address return value. Use NULL if unneeded.
.IP "align" 12
alignment in bytes for starting address
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate the requested number of zeroed bytes from the specified pool,
with the given alignment restriction. Can not be used in NMI handler on
architectures without NMI-safe cmpxchg implementation.
.SH "RETURN"
virtual address of the allocated zeroed memory, or NULL on failure
